additional_house_rules:
Guests agree to the following terms and conditions:

1) Guest(s) agree that NO PARTIES or EVENTS are to take place at the property at any time. Any action that cause damages to the unit, property, reputation, or relationship with building staff or other residents, will result in the expulsion of the guests and his or her group from the premises. 
2) There is NO SMOKING (of any kind) permitted in the unit or on the premises. 
3) Illegal drug use is strictly prohibited. This includes the use of marijuana or marijuana extracts regardless of any personal permit. 
4) Guests agree to abide by maximum occupancy of unit
5) Guests agree to observe quiet hours from 9:00 pm until 9:00 am
6) Guests accept complete responsibility for the unit from check-in until check-out. The registered guest is responsible for the actions of all members of his or her group. 
7) Guests agree to return all keys, remotes, and parking passes. Failure to return items will result in charges to the guest. 
8) Guests agree to pay replacement cost for any damaged, destroyed, or non-returned items.
9) Guests will be subject to a $100 per hour fee for unauthorized early check-in or late check-out. 
10) Any illegal activity or violation of the above terms may result in immediate expulsion from property. Such actions will be reported to Airbnb and local law enforcement. Guest is responsible for all costs associated with expulsion. 
11) Guests may be asked to agree and sign a rental agreement.
12) Guests may be asked to provide a date of birth as proof of age. (Traveler must be at least 21 years of age to make a reservation)
description:
2 bedroom apartment in the heart of Manhattan's lively West Village. Ideally located near Union Square, Flatiron District, Meatpacking District, Soho, Chelsea, and more. 

The West Village looks like a European small town in the middle of the nation’s biggest city.  Shoppers, diners, and art aficionados flock here in droves. Despite its foot-traffic, the West Village manages to maintain an intimate vibe that sets it apart from many of the other "hustle and bustle"  New York City destinations.

Perfect location. Great views. 1 minute walk to subway.

Entire apartment.

Just a text, email, or phone call away.

https://www.airbnb.com/locations/new-york/west-village

Subway, taxi, bus, all a short walk away.

hosts.about:
Hi!! Thank you for looking at my listing. I love to travel all over the world and renting my place out helps me accomplish this! 

I love sports - Basketball, tennis, Squash, Poker, and sometimes a little ping pong or juggling at the park. I also love eating all kinds of yummy food, going to shows, movies, and concerts. 

I love people and animals maybe even more, especially dogs. They are such a gift. 

I try not to plan everything and for the most part - I just do it!!

Additional Info - California demeanor, New York driven! Always striving to excel. I enjoy healthy foods, traveling, helping others and animals, and dancing. Favorite networks are CNBC, Animal Planet, and Discovery. Favorite shows are Homeland, Scandal, Shark Tank, Breaking Bad, The Americans, and watching the Chargers fumble on Sundays. I love people and I have met many wonderful people from all over the world through this business.

Hey there. I'm Greg. How's it going? 

About me: I'm an engineer, entrepreneur, athlete, musician, and your friendly Airbnb Host. I enjoy spending time in New York City, Boston, Nashville, New Orleans, San Francisco, Austin, Portland, Palm Springs, Los Angeles, and my hometown of San Diego.

I've done some traveling abroad in Costa Rica, Mexico, Thailand, China, Indonesia, Malayasia and Australia. I'm looking forward to visiting many of the countries in Western Europe in the near future. When I travel, I keep it light and don't require a whole lot. A comfortable place to rest my head, and a warm shower to soak my bones. (Ok, I need AC, laundry and WiFi too). 

I own property in multiple cities and host Airbnb users every day. When it comes to hosting, I see it as my job to welcome you warmly, provide what you need to help make your experience enjoyable, and stay out of your way (unless otherwise directed). 

Thanks for reading my profile. Now back to your regularly scheduled programming.

review.comments:
Our family of four could have spent $500-$600 a night for a  more fully-equipped flat with more amenities like washer, dryer, gourmet kitchen, etc. In fact, that's what we were planning on doing -- and what we have always done before.

But my wife suggested that we get something a bit more basic instead, around $250 per night for a 3 night stay. After all, we'd be out and about seeinmg the sights in New York all day and night, so it's not like we'd be hanging around the house all day. Anmd then, too, she liked the idea of having an extra $1,000 to spend on shopping.

She was right. We had a perfectly wonderful stay at Greg's $250/night flat, and didn't miss a gourmet kitchen or extra bedroom or washer and dryer one bit. The flat is wonderfully located, was clean and light and airy, and Greg went out of his way to make our stay comfortable -- buying us a small fan to help kill the street noise and letting us check out a bit later than required.

If you plan to be out and about during your New York visit, you couldn't ask for a better or more affordable pl;ace to saty than Greg's flat.
